The famous Blue Mosque of Istanbul a few minutes before sunrise. Getting up early meant beating the huge crowds and having this stunning view almost all to myself! 🕌

#istanbul #bluemosque #sunrise #europe #travel #mosque

The beautiful town of Dinant located in Southern Belgium on the banks of the River Meuse. The medieval citadel sits high atop the rock face behind the iconic cathedral overlooking the town.

#Belgium #Dinant #Europe

One of the biggest highlights from my recent trip was getting to spend some time at Gallipoli. A very historic place for Australians, this was the site of the landing and subsequent battles for Australian and New Zealand armed forces during World War One.
The area has many cemeteries but Lone Pine is one of the most famous. With its single towering pine tree watching over all of the fallen souls who rest beneath it. I even managed to find the grave of my relative who lays here, it was quite humbling to get to see this area first hand!

#Turkey #Gallipoli #lonepine #cemetery #ww1 #war #history #europe

Nightfall at the Grand Ortaköy Mosque and Istanbuls famous bridge connecting Europe to Asia 🌉

Looking down the river from Ponte Umberto towards St. Peter's Basilica and Vatican City. Not quite the fiery sunset that I was hoping for but I managed to blend a sunset and night photo together to capture all of the lights brightening up the bridge and the church.

The 4:30am wake-up was worth it yesterday to be the first hikers on this popular trail and get this beautiful sunrise to ourselves. 
By the time @bennyg_images and I left the trail there was literally hundreds of people making their way up to view the larch trees. Gotta love fall in Kananaskis! 🍁
